---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Header from '../components/layout/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/layout/Footer.astro';
import { companyConfig } from '../data/company';

const title = 'Accessibility Statement - Key Kings Locksmith';
const description = 'Key Kings Locksmith is committed to ensuring digital accessibility for people with disabilities. Learn about our accessibility efforts and WCAG compliance.';
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}>
  <Header />

  <main>
    <!-- Page Header -->
    <section class="bg-gradient-to-br from-gold-400 to-gold-600 text-charcoal-900 py-12">
      <div class="container mx-auto px-4">
        <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto text-center">
          <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold mb-4">Accessibility Statement</h1>
          <p class="text-lg text-charcoal-800">
            Last Updated: January 1, 2025
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Accessibility Content -->
    <section class="py-16">
      <div class="container mx-auto px-4">
        <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto prose prose-lg">

          <p class="lead">
            {companyConfig.name} is committed to ensuring digital accessibility for people with disabilities. We are continually improving the user experience for everyone and applying the relevant accessibility standards.
          </p>

          <h2>Our Commitment</h2>

          <p>We believe that everyone should have equal access to information and services, regardless of their abilities. We are dedicated to providing a website that is accessible to the widest possible audience, including those with visual, hearing, cognitive, or motor impairments.</p>

          <h2>Conformance Status</h2>

          <p>The Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG) define requirements for designers and developers to improve accessibility for people with disabilities. It defines three levels of conformance: Level A, Level AA, and Level AAA.</p>

          <p>Our website strives to conform to <strong>WCAG 2.1 Level AA</strong> standards. We are actively working to achieve and maintain this level of accessibility across all pages and features.</p>

          <h3>Current Compliance Status</h3>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Partially Conformant:</strong> Some parts of the content do not fully conform to WCAG 2.1 Level AA, but we are actively working to address these issues</li>
            <li>We conduct regular accessibility audits and testing</li>
            <li>We prioritize accessibility in all new features and updates</li>
          </ul>

          <h2>Accessibility Features</h2>

          <p>Our website includes the following accessibility features:</p>

          <h3>Navigation and Structure</h3>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Semantic HTML:</strong> Proper use of HTML5 semantic elements for clear document structure</li>
            <li><strong>Heading Hierarchy:</strong> Logical heading structure (H1-H6) for easy navigation</li>
            <li><strong>Skip Navigation:</strong> Skip links to bypass repetitive content and jump to main content</li>
            <li><strong>Keyboard Navigation:</strong> Full keyboard accessibility for all interactive elements</li>
            <li><strong>Focus Indicators:</strong> Visible focus indicators for keyboard navigation</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>Visual Design</h3>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Color Contrast:</strong> Text and background colors meet WCAG AA contrast ratios (4.5:1 for normal text, 3:1 for large text)</li>
            <li><strong>Resizable Text:</strong> Text can be resized up to 200% without loss of functionality</li>
            <li><strong>Responsive Design:</strong> Mobile-friendly layout that adapts to different screen sizes</li>
            <li><strong>No Color-Only Information:</strong> Information is not conveyed by color alone</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>Content and Media</h3>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Alternative Text:</strong> Descriptive alt text for all meaningful images</li>
            <li><strong>Link Purpose:</strong> Clear and descriptive link text that makes sense out of context</li>
            <li><strong>Form Labels:</strong> Proper labels and instructions for all form fields</li>
            <li><strong>Error Identification:</strong> Clear error messages and suggestions for correction</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>Interactive Elements</h3>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>ARIA Labels:</strong> Appropriate ARIA attributes for enhanced screen reader support</li>
            <li><strong>Button Accessibility:</strong> All buttons and controls are keyboard accessible</li>
            <li><strong>Form Validation:</strong> Accessible form validation with clear error messages</li>
            <li><strong>Modal Dialogs:</strong> Accessible modal windows with proper focus management</li>
          </ul>

          <h3>Motion and Animation</h3>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Reduced Motion:</strong> Respect for prefers-reduced-motion settings</li>
            <li><strong>No Auto-Play:</strong> No automatically playing audio or video</li>
            <li><strong>Pause Controls:</strong> Ability to pause, stop, or hide moving content</li>
          </ul>

          <h2>Assistive Technologies</h2>

          <p>Our website is designed to be compatible with the following assistive technologies:</p>

          <ul>
            <li><strong>Screen Readers:</strong> JAWS, NVDA, VoiceOver, TalkBack</li>
            <li><strong>Screen Magnification:</strong> ZoomText, MAGic, browser zoom</li>
            <li><strong>Speech Recognition:</strong> Dragon NaturallySpeaking, Voice Control</li>
            <li><strong>Keyboard Navigation:</strong> Full keyboard support without requiring a mouse</li>
          </ul>

          <h2>Browser Compatibility</h2>

          <p>Our website is tested and optimized for accessibility in the following browsers:</p>

          <ul>
            <li>Google Chrome (latest version)</li>
            <li>Mozilla Firefox (latest version)</li>
            <li>Apple Safari (latest version)</li>
            <li>Microsoft Edge (latest version)</li>
            <li>Mobile browsers: iOS Safari, Chrome Mobile</li>
          </ul>

          <h2>Known Limitations</h2>

          <p>Despite our best efforts, there may be some limitations. Below are known issues we are working to address:</p>

          <ul>
            <li><strong>Third-Party Content:</strong> Some third-party embedded content (maps, social media widgets) may not be fully accessible</li>
            <li><strong>PDF Documents:</strong> Some older PDF documents may not be fully accessible; we are working to remediate these</li>
            <li><strong>Legacy Content:</strong> Some older content may not meet current accessibility standards; we are systematically updating this content</li>
          </ul>

          <h2>Ongoing Efforts</h2>

          <p>We are committed to continuous improvement of our website's accessibility. Our ongoing efforts include:</p>

          <ul>
            <li>Regular accessibility audits using automated and manual testing</li>
            <li>User testing with people who use assistive technologies</li>
            <li>Training for our team on accessibility best practices</li>
            <li>Incorporating accessibility into our design and development process</li>
            <li>Monitoring and addressing accessibility issues as they are identified</li>
            <li>Staying current with WCAG guidelines and best practices</li>
          </ul>

          <h2>Feedback and Contact</h2>

          <p>We welcome your feedback on the accessibility of our website. If you encounter any accessibility barriers or have suggestions for improvement, please let us know:</p>

          <div class="not-prose bg-gold-50 rounded-lg p-6 my-6 border border-gold-200">
            <p class="font-semibold text-charcoal-900 mb-2">Accessibility Feedback</p>
            <p class="text-charcoal-700 mb-1">
              <strong>Email:</strong> <a href={`mailto:${companyConfig.contact.email.primary}`} class="text-gold-600 hover:text-gold-700 font-medium">{companyConfig.contact.email.primary}</a>
            </p>
            <p class="text-charcoal-700 mb-1">
              <strong>Phone:</strong> <a href={`tel:${companyConfig.contact.phone.formatted}`} class="text-gold-600 hover:text-gold-700 font-medium">{companyConfig.contact.phone.display}</a>
            </p>
            <p class="text-charcoal-700 mb-3">
              <strong>Mail:</strong> {companyConfig.contact.address.street}, {companyConfig.contact.address.city}, {companyConfig.contact.address.state} {companyConfig.contact.address.zipCode}
            </p>
            <p class="text-charcoal-600 text-sm">
              We aim to respond to accessibility feedback within 3 business days.
            </p>
          </div>

          <h3>What to Include in Your Feedback</h3>
          <p>When reporting an accessibility issue, please include:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>The specific page or feature where you encountered the issue</li>
            <li>A description of the problem</li>
            <li>The assistive technology you were using (if applicable)</li>
            <li>Your browser and operating system</li>
            <li>Any suggestions you have for improvement</li>
          </ul>

          <h2>Alternative Access</h2>

          <p>If you are unable to access any content or use any features on our website due to accessibility barriers, we are happy to provide alternative access:</p>

          <ul>
            <li><strong>Phone Support:</strong> Call us at <a href={`tel:${companyConfig.contact.phone.formatted}`} class="text-gold-600 hover:text-gold-700 font-medium">{companyConfig.contact.phone.display}</a> for assistance</li>
            <li><strong>Email Support:</strong> Email us at <a href={`mailto:${companyConfig.contact.email.primary}`} class="text-gold-600 hover:text-gold-700 font-medium">{companyConfig.contact.email.primary}</a> with your request</li>
            <li><strong>In-Person Service:</strong> Visit our location for in-person assistance</li>
          </ul>

          <h2>Technical Specifications</h2>

          <p>Accessibility of our website relies on the following technologies:</p>

          <ul>
            <li>HTML5</li>
            <li>CSS3</li>
            <li>JavaScript (with graceful degradation)</li>
            <li>WAI-ARIA (Accessible Rich Internet Applications)</li>
          </ul>

          <h2>Assessment and Testing</h2>

          <p>Our website has been assessed using the following methods:</p>

          <ul>
            <li><strong>Self-Evaluation:</strong> Internal accessibility audits by our development team</li>
            <li><strong>Automated Testing:</strong> Tools such as WAVE, axe DevTools, and Lighthouse</li>
            <li><strong>Manual Testing:</strong> Keyboard navigation, screen reader testing, and color contrast verification</li>
            <li><strong>User Testing:</strong> Feedback from users with disabilities</li>
          </ul>

          <h2>Formal Complaints</h2>

          <p>If you are not satisfied with our response to your accessibility concern, you may file a formal complaint:</p>

          <ul>
            <li>Contact us in writing at the address above</li>
            <li>Include detailed information about the accessibility barrier</li>
            <li>Describe the steps you have already taken to resolve the issue</li>
          </ul>

          <p>We will investigate all formal complaints and respond within 10 business days.</p>

          <h2>Legal Information</h2>

          <p>This accessibility statement applies to the website located at keykingslocksmithsc.com. It was prepared in accordance with:</p>

          <ul>
            <li>Americans with Disabilities Act (ADA)</li>
            <li>Section 508 of the Rehabilitation Act</li>
            <li>Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG) 2.1</li>
          </ul>

          <h2>Updates to This Statement</h2>

          <p>We will update this accessibility statement as we make improvements to our website. This statement was last reviewed and updated on January 1, 2025.</p>

          <hr class="my-8" />

          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 italic">
            We are committed to making our website accessible to all users. Thank you for helping us improve accessibility by sharing your feedback.
          </p>

        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>
